data.text:
Share This:

I'm looking for information on James Cronin and Mary Margaret Sullivan. I'd love to find out more about them, especially who James' parents were, so I can continue this branch of my family tree. Here's the information I have.

James Cronin

Born 15 Jun 1860 in Listowel, Ireland

Died 05 Apr 1927 in Cook County, Illinois

Death certificate lists Mary McNamara as his mother, but that's Mary Sullivan's mother

Emmigrated to the US in 1883

Married Mary Sullivan in 1886 (in Chicago, IL)

Mary Margaret Sullivan (possibly Margaret Mary Sullivan?)

Born 8 Oct 1863 in Kerry, Ireland (not sure if it was Listowel)

One source lists her from Skehenerin, Listowel, Kerry, Ireland

Died 13 May 1932 in Cook County, Illinois

Death certificate lists Michael Sullivan and Mary McNamara as parents

Emmigrated to the US in 1881

Message Board Replies

Topher:

You may want to search www.irishgenealogy.ie That site has a lot of Co. Kerry church records. Looked at Listowel records. No James Cronin in 1860 but a James in June 1859. You can also search for Mary Margaret in Listowel and across Co. Kerry.

Roger McDonnell

Castlemore Roscommon, IrelandXO Volunteer ☘
